stylometry: The tradeoff on how much to order is between holding costs and order costs. The decison is to order small amounts frequently or large amounts infrequently. A compnay needs to determine when to order and how much so they dont run out and profit is maximized. When ordering a large amount infrequently it lowers the order costs becasue more inventory is ordered at once saving on the costs it takes to delever and order, but could also rise inventory costs depending on the time it takes to sell and the demand. If they choose to order smaller amounts frequently, the order costs will be higher but the holding costs will be less. The Economic Order Quantity equalizes these tradeoffs by finding the optimization for the company depending on factors such as order costs, shortage penalty, holding costs, demand - and minimizes both costs.
